39
00:03:05.560 --> 00:03:09.410
40% of esophageal gastric adenocarcinoma and

40
00:03:09.440 --> 00:03:12.820
has very poor survival outcomes and resistance to systemic treatment.

41
00:03:14.060 --> 00:03:17.220
Mesothelin is overexpressed in up to 60% of esophageal gastric

42
00:03:17.260 --> 00:03:21.180
adenocarcinoma and associated with very aggressive disease biology in

43
00:03:21.300 --> 00:03:24.860
stage four patients, and we know that mesothelin has low levels of

44
00:03:24.920 --> 00:03:26.740
expression in normal tissues.

45
00:03:27.820 --> 00:03:31.700
Our group designed M28 Zeta-1XXPD1-DNR, which is an

46
00:03:31.780 --> 00:03:35.200
autologous mesothelin-targeted CAR, which features a

47
00:03:35.560 --> 00:03:39.200
CD28 costimulatory domain as well as a modified CD3

48
00:03:39.300 --> 00:03:43.190
zeta and a PD-1 dominant negative receptor which lacks an

49
00:03:43.880 --> 00:03:47.480
intracellular signaling domain, and this provides intrinsic

50
00:03:47.490 --> 00:03:49.350
checkpoint blockade to the CAR T cells.

51
00:03:51.220 --> 00:03:53.440
Here we have data from our preclinical studies,

52
00:03:54.460 --> 00:03:58.420
where we have orthotopic mouse model

53
00:03:59.300 --> 00:04:02.680
which mimics human peritoneal carcinomatosis

54
00:04:03.680 --> 00:04:06.900
and manifests with ascites as well as bowel obstruction.

55
00:04:07.460 --> 00:04:11.180
And we can see that regional delivery of the mesothelin-targeted CAR T

56
00:04:11.200 --> 00:04:14.500
cells conferred better efficacy as well as survival outcomes

57
00:04:14.980 --> 00:04:18.760
compared to systemic delivery of higher doses of the same CAR T cells in

58
00:04:18.800 --> 00:04:19.421
these mice.

59
00:04:20.399 --> 00:04:24.220
Our group has also previously demonstrated that regional intrapleural

60
00:04:24.300 --> 00:04:27.560
delivery of a previous generation of M28 Zeta

61
00:04:28.100 --> 00:04:31.980
mesothelin-targeted CAR T cells in combination with systemic

62
00:04:32.100 --> 00:04:35.660
anti-PD-1 therapy with pembrolizumab was safe and efficacious in

63
00:04:35.720 --> 00:04:37.420
patients with pleural disease.

64
00:04:38.800 --> 00:04:42.280
So in this study, it was a phase one study assessing the safety,

65
00:04:42.680 --> 00:04:46.380
maximum tolerated dose, and preliminary efficacy of

66
00:04:46.460 --> 00:04:50.380
IP-administered mesothelin-targeted CAR in patients with mesothelin

67
00:04:50.480 --> 00:04:54.340
positive defined as more than 25% positive by

68
00:04:54.360 --> 00:04:57.300
immunohistochemistry with evidence of peritoneal

69
00:04:57.320 --> 00:04:58.380
