815
00:49:55.622 --> 00:49:58.672
The overall survival benefit observed in these first-line

816
00:49:58.712 --> 00:50:02.692
patients was very predominantly due to tobentafusp rather than subsequent

817
00:50:02.752 --> 00:50:03.372
therapies.

818
00:50:04.352 --> 00:50:07.932
On the tobentafusp arm, nearly half of the patients had only received

819
00:50:07.952 --> 00:50:11.902
tobentafusp, and the five-year survivors on the investigator's choice arm,

820
00:50:12.032 --> 00:50:15.972
86% of them had actually received subsequent tobentafusp.

821
00:50:17.132 --> 00:50:21.012
The overall survival favored tobentafusp across most patient subgroups,

822
00:50:21.482 --> 00:50:25.472
with benefit observed regardless of disease location or baseline

823
00:50:25.532 --> 00:50:26.852
metastatic tumor size.

824
00:50:27.992 --> 00:50:31.532
Early ctDNA molecular response continues to be a more sensitive marker

825
00:50:32.112 --> 00:50:35.452
of tobentafusp activity than radiographic measurements.

826
00:50:36.252 --> 00:50:39.952
And patients who continued tobentafusp beyond initial radiographic progression

827
00:50:40.492 --> 00:50:44.012
experienced longer post-progression survival compared to those who stopped

828
00:50:44.052 --> 00:50:45.492
treatment, even when accounting for

829
00:50:47.612 --> 00:50:49.552
variations in baseline characteristics.

830
00:50:51.552 --> 00:50:55.522
Finally, we'd like to thank all patients, their families, and their

